snippet: The Federal Reserve reported that factory output decreased by 0.4 percent in May.
abstract: Federal Reserve announces that factory output contracted 0.4 percent in May, the second contraction in three months; new data is the latest in a series of reports portraying a weak economy that have led analysts to cut growth forecasts while raising expectations that the Federal Reserve will offer new stimulus measures.
lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve reported that factory output decreased by 0.4 percent in May.
